title: Fishtown Coffee Tour
description: Fishtown is home to multiple roasters and unique coffee shops, sporting local fare and eclectic atmospheres.

title: Colonial Philadelphia History Tour
description: Explore the history of colonial Philadelphia by exploring some of our nation's earliest landmarks.

title: Explore University City
description: The University of Pennsylvania, Drexel University, the University of the Sciences and the Restaurant School at Walnut Hill College all share turf here, in the city's bustling, culturally diverse academic heart. Cutting-edge exhibitions at the Institute of Contemporary Art attract hip crowds. Budget-friendly dining options include street food stalls and international eateries, and there are plenty of casual bars.

title: Northern Liberties Fun!
description: This former industrial area, revitalized by artists in the 1990s, is now a hipster hotspot pulsing with art galleries and trendy boutiques. Built on the site of an old brewery, The Piazza is a shopping and dining complex located under luxury apartments. Locals head to North 2nd Street for global restaurants, craft beer halls and dance clubs, or to the Liberties Walk pedestrian mall for bike paths and unique shops.

title: Parkway Must See
description: Logan Square’s personality defies a single definition. It combines corporate and municipal office buildings and luxury high-rises with modern and historic houses along tree-lined side streets. Museums bordering the wide Benjamin Franklin Parkway add yet another dimension. Green spaces — including the area’s namesake — provide spots for relaxation, reflection and fun.
